start.label: it's better to ask forgiveness than permission

examples.en: He gave his approval to our plan.
I met approval in her look.
He was tricked into approval.
We received their approval to continue the research.
The crowd gave a yell of approval.
He nodded his approval.
He grunted his reluctant approval
They clapped their hands in approval.
Words of approval seldom passed his lips.
Do I have your approval to make the changes?
Mankind had stamped its approval upon certain actions.
The proposal has won the approval of the city council.
He basked in his employer's approval.
The president has already given his approval to the plan.
His decision merited the approval of any sensible person.
We were required to get approvals at each stage of the project.
As you may recall, we had agreed that decisions would require prior approval.
A murmur of approval passed through the crowd.
The President's approval rating has plunged to 20 percent.
Does the design meet with your approval (=do you like it?)?
She looked to Greg for approval.
Eighty percent of the vote was the threshold for approval of the plan.
A characteristic of the feminine psyche is to seek approval from others.
The plan was given qualified approval.
The government has so far withheld approval of the drug.
The government has given provisional approval for the use of the new drug.
The IMF has given its seal of approval to the government's economic strategy.
The President would appoint the Council of Ministers, subject to the approval of the National Assembly.
The crowd roared its approval.
His approval was an added fillip.
